The middle-out compression engine — stage 2 of the pipeline. The crown jewels of Pied Piper.

# lang Python {#py_lang}

Python 3.12+, standard library only, executed as a plain script (`python3 compressor.py`). PEP 8 style.

# good Typed Python {#py_patterns}

- Every function signature carries full type hints (parameters and return type).
- Module-level constants for the service name and error codes — no magic strings repeated inline.
- The `if __name__ == "__main__":` guard wraps the entry point so the module stays importable for tests.

# dep {#py_deps}

Python standard library only — `json`, `sys`, `datetime` and friends. No `pip install`, no `requirements.txt`.
